id: 5dca6047-24ed-4eb7-b44e-ec7f1bf42621
name: Detect Outbound LDAP Traffic(ASIM Network Session schema)
description: |
  'Malicious actors often abuse misconfigured LDAP servers or applications that use the LDAP servers in organizations. Outbound LDAP traffic should not be allowed outbound through your perimeter firewall. This search will help determine if you have any LDAP connections to IP addresses outside of private (RFC1918) address space.'
tags:
  - Schema: ASimNetworkSessions
    SchemaVersion: 0.2.4
requiredDataConnectors: []
tactics:
  - Initial Access
  - Execution
relevantTechniques:
  - T1071
  - T1059
query: |
_Im_NetworkSession
| where TimeGenerated > ago(1d) and EventResult != "Failure"
| where ipv4_is_private(SrcIpAddr) and not(ipv4_is_private(DstIpAddr)) and SrcIpAddr != DstIpAddr
| where tostring(DstPortNumber) has_any ("389", "636")
| summarize Starttime= min(TimeGenerated),EndTime= max(TimeGenerated),Eventscount=sum(EventCount), EventVendors=make_set(EventVendor,10) by SrcIpAddr,DstIpAddr,DstPortNumber,NetworkProtocol,EventResult
